# Testing Patterns

## Framework
Vitest for unit tests. Integration tests use bash scripts with curl and TypeScript scripts.

## Unit Test Structure
```typescript
import { describe, expect, it, vi, beforeEach } from "vitest";

describe("Feature", () => {
  beforeEach(() => { vi.clearAllMocks(); });

  it("should do something", async () => {
    // Arrange → Act → Assert
  });
});
```

## Mocking the Database
```typescript
const createMockDb = () => {
  const db: Record<string, any> = {
    query: {
      users: { findFirst: vi.fn() },
      profiles: { findFirst: vi.fn() },
      organizationMembers: { findFirst: vi.fn(), findMany: vi.fn() },
    },
    select: vi.fn(),
    update: vi.fn(),
  };
  db.transaction = vi.fn(async (fn: (tx: any) => Promise<any>) => fn(db));
  return db;
};
```

## Mock GraphQL Context
```typescript
const createMockContext = (): GraphQLContext => ({
  userId: "test-user-id",
  organizationId: "test-org-id",  // NOT orgId
  role: "MEMBER",
  email: "test@example.com",
  providerSubject: "workos-123",
  claims: {},
  requestId: "test-request-id",
  db: createMockDb() as any,
  loaders: createMockLoaders() as any,
});
```

## Rules
- Test files: `tests/unit/{domain}/{feature}.test.ts`
- Mock external services (DB, S3, Sentry) — never hit real infra in unit tests
- `transaction` mock must pass the same mock object as `tx` to the callback
- `auditResolver`-wrapped resolvers take 4 args: `(parent, args, context, info)` — pass `{} as any` for `info` in tests
- `createMockContext` should accept optional overrides for flexible test setup
- Run `pnpm check` before committing (lint + typecheck + tests)
